    "body": "## Summary\n\n- Move backend-specific atomic add, reduce, finalize reducer, and sparse GEMM lowering out of shared TileOp implementations.\n- Add backend registration files for CPU, CUDA, ROCm, Metal, and WebGPU reducer paths, plus CUDA and ROCm boundaries for atomic add and sparse GEMM.\n- Add a Python GEMM_SP backend registry and CUDA registration for the sparse GEMM Python path.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `./format.sh` (pre-commit hooks passed; the script reported unstaged changes before commit)\n- `cmake -S . -B build`\n- `cmake --build build -j$(nproc)`\n- `PYTHONPATH=$(pwd) python -m pytest testing/python/language/test_tilelang_language_reduce.py -q`\n- `PYTHONPATH=$(pwd) python -m pytest testing/python/language/test_tilelang_language_atomic.py -q -k \"test_atomic_add or test_tile_atomic_add or test_tma_atomic_add\"`\n- `PYTHONPATH=$(pwd) python -m pytest testing/python/language/test_tilelang_language_reduce_maxmin_nan.py -q`\n- `PYTHONPATH=$(pwd) python -m pytest testing/python/issue/test_tilelang_issue_tma_no_ws.py::test_sparse_ws_regular_metadata_copy_stays_in_producer testing/python/issue/test_tilelang_issue_ws_simt_copy_full_producer_extent.py::test_ws_keeps_full_producer_extent_for_lowered_simt_copy -q`\n\n## Notes\n\nThe ROCm backend files are included, but this environment was configured for CUDA, so the ROCm-specific CMake build still needs a ROCm runner.\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Added backend-specific lowerings: CUDA/ROCm/Metal/WebGPU/CPU implementations for GEMM_SP, cumsum, fill, transpose, atomic_add/atomic_reduce, reduce, and finalize_reducer; Python-side backend registration for GEMM_SP.\n\n* **Refactor**\n  * Pluggable backend dispatch introduced across many ops (reduce, fill, transpose, finalize_reducer, atomic_add/reduce, gemm_sp), enabling target-specific implementations and runtime selection.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
